.. _continuous-ncx2: Noncentral chi-squared Distribution =================================== The distribution of :math:`\sum_{i=1}^{
u}\left(Z_{i}+\delta_{i}ight)^{2}` where :math:`Z_{i}` are independent standard normal variables and :math:`\delta_{i}` are constants. :math:`\lambda=\sum_{i=1}^{
u}\delta_{i}^{2}>0.` (In communications it is called the Marcum-Q function). It can be thought of as a Generalized Rayleigh-Rice distribution. The two shape parameters are :math:`
u`, a positive integer, and :math:`\lambda`, a positive real number. The support is :math:`x\geq0`. .. math:: :nowrap:  egin{eqnarray*} f\left(x;
u,\lambdaight) & = & e^{-\left(\lambda+xight)/2} rac{1}{2}\left( rac{x}{\lambda}ight)^{\left(
u-2ight)/4}I_{\left(
u-2ight)/2}\left(\sqrt{\lambda x}ight)\ F\left(x;
u,\lambdaight) & = & \sum_{j=0}^{\infty}\left\{  rac{\left(\lambda/2ight)^{j}}{j!}e^{-\lambda/2}ight\} \mathrm{Pr}\left[\chi_{
u+2j}^{2}\leq xight]\ G\left(q;
u,\lambdaight) & = & F^{-1}\left(q;
u,\lambdaight)\ \mu & = & 
u+\lambda\ \mu_{2} & = & 2\left(
